<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="#">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/dist/output.css">
    <title>Marie Groceries</title>
</head>
<%- include('partials/nav-bar.ejs') %>
<body class="bg-slate-500 text-center">
    <div class="grid text-center">
        <p class=" text-3xl text-slate-100 mx-auto mt-5">Por favor pide lo que quieras:</p>
    </div>
    <!--God practice with a for loop to not repeat divs and code -->
    <form class="grid w-full grid-cols-3 grid-rows-2 text-center py-5 justify-center" action="/buy/carrito" method="POST">
        <%for(product of products){%>
            <div class="row-span-2 justify-center p-5 bg-slate-600 rounded-xl w-2/3 ml-20 shadow-xl mt-5">
                <div class=" hover:bg-gray-700 shadow-xl rounded-xl">
                    <img class="mx-auto" src="<%=product.imagen%>" alt="Image">
                </div>
                <div class="mt-3 mx-auto w-2/4 bg-slate-500 rounded-lg shadow-xl">
                    <input class="cursor-pointer" id="<%=product.nombre%>" type="checkbox" name="<%=product.nombre%>">
                    <label class="text-zinc-200" for="<%=product.nombre%>"><%=product.nombre%> $<%=product.precio%></label>
                </div>
            </div>
        <% } %>
    </div>
    <div class="py-10 text-xl">
        <input class="p-5 bg-slate-400 text-zinc-100 cursor-pointer rounded-lg" type="submit" value="Ir a carrito" class="btn btn-primary text-center">
    </div>
    <% if(last_added_product != '') { %>
        <div class="py-10 text-xl">
            Last added product, was: <%= last_added_product%>
            The pros of using a software architecture type of MVC (Model View Controller)
            architecture which uses a flow between a model, a controller and a view...
            The model notifies de controller, then the controller updates the views, 
            followed by a user action which is called in the controller and updates the model.
            In real scenarios, the model just fetches data from database, insert it, update it, etc.
            Model is where XML, HTML, CSS files are and which the customer/user interacts with.
            Controller is in charge of processing the data after the request of a view and before 
            updating something in the database with our Model.
            <ul>
                <h1 class="text-2xl">PROS</h1>
                <li class="list-disc">Development of app becomes fast</li>
                <li class="list-disc">Easy to collaborate between various programmers</li>
                <li class="list-disc">Easier to Debug as we have multiple levels to look at</li>
                <h1 class="text-2xl">CONS</h1>
                <li class="list-disc">Strict rules on methdos</li>
                <li class="list-disc">It's hard to understand MVC architecture</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    <% } %>
</form>
</body>